If you have [embedded checkout](/paid-subscriptions) enabled, your subscribers can purchase paid subscriptions as gifts for others directly from your subscribe page.

{% iframe src="https://buttondown.com/justin" height=800 /%}

## How it works

When someone visits your subscribe page, they'll see a checkbox labeled **"This is a gift"** next to the email address field. When checked, additional fields appear:

| Field                         | Description                                                                                                 |
|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Purchaser's email**        | The buyer enters their own email address for billing purposes and payment receipts.                       |
| **Recipient's email** | A new field appears where the purchaser can enter the email address of the person who will receive the subscription. |
| **Gift message**   | The purchaser can optionally add a personal message that will be included when the recipient is notified about their gift subscription. |


After payment is completed, the subscription is created for the recipient's email address, not the purchaser's. The recipient receives a notification email letting them know they've been gifted a subscription.

## How gift subscriptions appear in your dashboard

These gift subscriptions appear exactly like regular premium subscriptions in your dashboard — you'll see the recipient as a premium subscriber with full access to your paid content. The only difference is that the subscription metadata includes information about who purchased it as a gift, which you can view in the subscriber's details.

